---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Reviewer Kit | BeaconGuard Due Diligence Materials"
  description="BeaconGuard Reviewer Kit for executive, architecture, security, evidence, and deployment-responsibility reviews using ALLOW/DENY semantics and Verifiable Decision Records."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Reviewer Kit</h1>
    <p class="lead">Policy control before governed execution. Evidence after every decision.</p>
    <p>
      Use this kit to review BeaconGuard as a Runtime Control Boundary that evaluates trusted request context against an Active Verified Release and returns ALLOW or DENY before governed execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>10-minute executive review</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/">Homepage business case and Product Overview</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/platform">Platform capability overview</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/design-partner-program">Controlled Evaluation offer</a> — available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>30-minute architecture review</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/architecture">System Architecture</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/how-it-works">How It Works runtime sequence</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/overview">Documentation overview</a> — available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Security review</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/security">Security page</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/threat-model">Threat Model</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/enforcement-runtime">Enforcement Runtime</a> — available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Evidence review</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/proof-evidence">Proof and Evidence samples</a> — sample</li>
      <li><a href="/sample-decision-record">Sample Decision Record</a> — sample</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/compliance-audit">Compliance and Audit</a> — available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Deployment responsibility review</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/control-responsibility-matrix">Control Responsibility Matrix</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/deployment">Deployment overview</a> — available</li>
      <li><a href="/docs/deployment-integration">Deployment and Integration</a> — available</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Controlled-evaluation prerequisites</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>One bounded workflow</li>
      <li>Representative request contract and required trust context</li>
      <li>Desired Compliance Playbook controls</li>
      <li>Deployment assumptions and identity-provider context</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Customer-specific architecture-fit memos and sample mappings are controlled-access outputs of a Controlled Evaluation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>What reviewers can assess</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>How ALLOW and DENY decisions are returned</li>
      <li>How Active Verified Releases govern evaluation</li>
      <li>What a Verifiable Decision Record contains</li>
      <li>Where customer and BeaconGuard responsibilities divide</li>
      <li>What remains out of scope for BeaconGuard</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/design-partner-program">Request Controlled Evaluation</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/trust-assurance">Open Trust Center</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
